      "span_text": "Nonfasted male Sprague-Dawley rats (356 Ϯ 17 g, 10 weeks old) from Charles River Laboratories (Sulzfeld, Germany) were cannulated for CPB as previously reported.  Briefly, the tail artery was cannulated for aortic inflow, the right external jugular vein was cannulated for venous return, and the right superficial caudal epigastric artery was cannulated for monitoring of mean arterial blood pressure (MAP)."
